# Coding conventions

These are non-negotiable structural rules for this codebase. Follow them for
every UI change. See `ARCHITECTURE.md` for the full map.

## 1. New screens → their own route + their own entry in `src/screens/`

- A "screen" is a full page (a navbar tab or a project/experience/game detail
  page). It must **not** be a component swapped into the existing page.
- Every new screen gets its **own route** registered in `src/App.js` (React
  Router) and its **own folder** `src/screens/<Name>/` with paired
  `<Name>.js` + (optional) `<Name>.css`.
- Screens compose reusable components; they are the only place page-specific
  layout lives. Navigating between screens must go through a route change
  (use `<AppLink>` / router links, never a full page reload for internal paths).

## 2. New components → reusable, in `src/components/`

- Every new component goes in `src/components/<Name>/` as paired
  `<Name>.js` + `<Name>.css`, with a JSDoc prop header.
- Components must be **generic and reusable**: all content comes in via props,
  no hard-coded page copy. If you find yourself writing screen-specific text or
  data inside a component, lift it to the screen or to `src/content/`.
- Reuse before you build: check `src/components/` for an existing component
  (e.g. `ProjectCard`, `CardGrid`, `Section`, `Tag`) before adding a new one.

## 3. Colors → primitives / semantic token files only

- **Never hard-code a color** (hex, rgb, hsl, named) in a component or screen
  CSS. Always use a semantic token: `var(--color-*)`.
- To add a color: add the raw value as a **primitive** in
  `src/styles/tokens/primitives.css` (a `--<family>-<step>` ramp value), then
  map it to a **semantic role** in `src/styles/tokens/semantic.css`
  (`--color-*`), wiring both the light `:root` and the dark
  `prefers-color-scheme` block. Components consume only the semantic token.

## Quick checklist before committing UI work

- [ ] New page? → routed in `App.js` **and** a folder in `src/screens/`.
- [ ] New component? → in `src/components/`, prop-driven, JSDoc'd, reusable.
- [ ] Any new color? → added to `primitives.css` + `semantic.css`, consumed via `var(--color-*)`.
- [ ] No hard-coded hex/rgb in component or screen CSS.
